<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Finland: Karelia borealis, Kitee: 1♂, Puhos [
<geoCoordinate degrees="62.082" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55" value="62.082">62.082°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="29.935" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="55" value="29.935">29.935°E</geoCoordinate>
], 30.06.2017, leg. Juha Salokannel. 1♀, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pajarinmäki">Pajarinmaeki</normalizedToken>
, 16.06.2020, YKJ grid coordinates: 68898:36667 [
<geoCoordinate degrees="62.078" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55" value="62.078">62.078°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="30.191" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="55" value="30.191">30.191°E</geoCoordinate>
], leg. Jaakko 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pohjoismäki">Pohjoismaeki</normalizedToken>
and M. Mutanen. 3♂, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pajarinmäki">Pajarinmaeki</normalizedToken>
, 18.06.2021, YKJ grid coordinates: 68898:36667 [
<geoCoordinate degrees="62.078" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55" value="62.078">62.078°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="30.191" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="55" value="30.191">30.191°E</geoCoordinate>
], leg. A. Liston, M. Mutanen, N. Kiljunen, M. Prous. Approximately 30 larvae, on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Insecta" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Sambucus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sambucus racemosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Sambucus racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pajarinmäki">Pajarinmaeki</normalizedToken>
, 26.07.2021, YKJ grid coordinates: 68898:36667 [
<geoCoordinate degrees="62.078" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55" value="62.078">62.078°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="30.191" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="55" value="30.191">30.191°E</geoCoordinate>
], leg. M. Mutanen and M. Prous. All specimens in ZMUO (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Macrophya infumata Rohwer, 1925. A. ♀ (ZMUO. 046055); B. ♂ (ZMUO. 060982)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719549" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">38</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719549" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figure 38" startId="F38">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Figure 38.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohwer" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Macrophya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrophya infumata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infumata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Macrophya infumata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rohwer, 1925. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A.</emphasis>
♀ (ZMUO.046055); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">B.</emphasis>
♂ (ZMUO.060982).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
In Europe previously recorded from the Russian regions of Kirov and Perm (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhelochovtsev, AN" journalOrPublisher="Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="357 - 379" refId="B200" refString="Zhelochovtsev, AN, Zinovjev, AG, 1996. Spisok pilil'shhikov i rogohvostov (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) fauny Rossii i sopredel'nyh territorij. II. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 75 (2): 357 - 379" title="Spisok pilil'shhikov i rogohvostov (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) fauny Rossii i sopredel'nyh territorij. II." volume="75" year="1996">Zhelochovtsev and Zinovjev 1996</bibRefCitation>
), but in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hellen, W" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" publicationUrl="https://www.inaturalist.org/taxa/564975-Macrophya-infumata" refId="B69" refString="2022. . https://www.inaturalist.org/taxa/564975-Macrophya-infumata" url="https://www.inaturalist.org/taxa/564975-Macrophya-infumata" year="2022">iNaturalist (2022)</bibRefCitation>
more western Russian records are to be found (Kursk, Moscow, and St Peterburg Regions). The species is widespread in the East Palaearctic, from W. Siberia to Sakhalin, Japan, and northern China (
<bibRefCitation author="Mallach, N" journalOrPublisher="Peiping" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="217 - 222" refId="B129" refString="Mallach, N, 1936. Dritter Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Blattwespenfauna Chinas. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, Zoology. Peiping 6: 217 - 222" title="Dritter Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Blattwespenfauna Chinas. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, Zoology." volume="6" year="1936">Mallach 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshida, H" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" publicationUrl="https://symphyta.jimdo.com/" refId="B195" refString="Yoshida, H, 2017. Checklist of Japanese Symphyta. Ver. 3.11. (7.IV.2017). https://symphyta.jimdo.com/" title="Checklist of Japanese Symphyta. Ver. 3.11. (7. IV. 2017)." url="https://symphyta.jimdo.com/" year="2017">Yoshida 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Host plant is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Insecta" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Sambucus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sambucus racemosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Sambucus racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the closely related Japanese 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. sieboldiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="sieboldiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">S. sieboldiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.26.325" author="Sakurai, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="325 - 329" refId="B160" refString="Sakurai, A, Hamanishi, Y, Maeto, K, Naito, C, 2009. Molecular biogeography of two sibling species of the sawfly genus Macrophya (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae) in Japan. Zoological Science 26 (5): 325 - 329, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.26.325" title="Molecular biogeography of two sibling species of the sawfly genus Macrophya (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae) in Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.26.325" volume="26" year="2009">Sakurai et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae were beaten from lower branches of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. racemosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">S. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a shady habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
